<h2>Abilities and Dice sets</h2><p>
A warrior can use one ability during their activation if the player controlling them has the correct dice set to do so. The Ability can be used before or after their first action, or after their second action.
	If an Ability lists a bonus action this is in addition to the 2 actions a warrior can make during their activation 
	Once the warrior has used the ability discard the  dice set. You can use a higher dice set for a lower requirement ability, e.g a quad could be used as a double or a triple. But you still have to discard the whole set even if you only used part of it (e.g.a quad cannot be used as two doubles)
	If the ability asks for the value of the dice set it refers to the numerical value on the dice, e.g a double six value is six. 
	Desperate last stand
If the warrior is the last left standing you can use as many abilities on them as you have dice sets for.
All Warbands can choose from the Universal Ability set, as well as the Warband specific ones. 
</p>
