<h2>Other rules</h2>
<p>
<h3>Falling Damage </h3>
For each full or partial 3” a warrior falls roll a D6 (e.g 4” fall rolls 2 dice)<br>
<em>1-2:</em> Take 1 Damage<br>
<em>3-4:</em> Take D3 Damage<br>
<em>5-6:</em> Take 3 Damage<br>
All falling damage ignores armour soaking. 

If a warrior is hit by any critical hits and is within ½” of an edge roll an Agility test for each of those critical hits, If any fail the warrior falls. The opponent that caused them to fall can choose any point within 2” of directly below the nearest edge to the falling warrior and this is where they land. 
The falling warrior rolls fall damage as above.
 </p>
<p>
<h3>Cover</h3>If there is any scenery between a warrior and his target that blocks full view of the target, then the target counts as +1 to the toughness for those attack actions. 
A target also counts as in cover if it is 3” or more higher than the attacking warrior.
</p> 

<h3>All Alone</h3>
<p>
If a warrior starts its activation in combat with 2 or more opponents and there are no friendly warriors within 3” then they must take a Bravery test, adding +1 per enemy over the first within 3” of them. 
If they fail they must use their first action to make a move action to get as far away from the opponents as possible (this will illicit free attacks as it is not a disengage action) and cannot end within 1” of the enemy. If this cannot be achieved the action is lost.
For their second action they must take a second bravery check without the penalties of the first (unless they are trapped in combat, then adding +1 per enemy over the first within 3” of them). If they pass this test they may act normal for their second action, if they fail again they must flee again and can only make a move action and must not end their action within 1” of an enemy warrior.
</p>
<h3>Fear</h3>
<p>
	The each time a warrior enters into combat with an enemy warrior that causes fear they must make a bravery test, if they fail the fear causing enemy counts as having +1 Toughness for the rest of the turn against that warrior.
	If a warrior causes fear they are also immune to fear from other warriors. Fear causing warriors count as double the count of warriors for outnumbering modification purposes unless the warrior in question also causes fear. (e.g a warrior in combat with an enemy warrior and a fear causing enemy warrior would have a +2 penalty on their bravery check) 
</p>
<h3>Hatred</h3>
<p>If a Warrior has hatred, when they are attacking their hated enemy in close combat for the first attack action (when they initially come into contact with that enemy) they can re-roll any missed attacks. After the initial hate filled burst combat returns to normal.
</p>
