<h2>Combat Rules</h2>
<h3>Dual wielding</h3>
<p>
Dual wielding a second One handed weapon is possible, as long as both weapons are one handed and the Warrior is not using a shield, when making an attack action add half (rounded up) of the second weapons Number of attacks to the attack action. <br> For Example: Wielding a mace in one hand and an axe in the other, You would get a total of 6 attack in an attack action (4+2) with only the axe attacks benefitting from penetrating, and needing to do at least the enemies Toughness worth of wounds with the mace attacks to allow clubbed to function.
<br> You also benefit from any weapon abilities, roll these attacks separately/with another coloured dice to distinguish.<br> 
Dual wielding Swords lets you parry twice.
</p>
<h3>Knocked down and Stunning</h3>
<p>
If a warrior takes more than their Toughness worth of wounds in one enemy activation and is still alive then there is a chance they may be Knocked down or Stunned. Roll a dice. <br>
<em>1-2</em> Warrior is fine and continues as normal<br>
<em>3-4</em> <strong>Knocked Down</strong>, Wounded warrior loses 1 activation next time they are activated. Enemies get +1 str when attacking the knocked down enemy<br>
<em>5-6</em> <strong>Stunned</strong>, Warrior loses entire activation next time they are activated. Enemies get a +2 str when attacking the Stunned enemy<br>
</p>
<h3>Strength and Armour Penetration</h3>
<p>Some blows are just too strong for even armour to deal with.
 If a warrior is attacking with a Strength of 5, they ignore one point of armour soak, a strength of 6+ they ignore two points of armour soak.
</p>
<h3>0 Wounds</h3>
<p>When a warrior is reduced to 0 wounds the attacking player rolls a dice for the warrior in question, add +1 for each additional point of damage that takes the warrior below 0:<br>
<em>1-2</em> <strong>Knocked Down</strong>, Wounded warrior loses 1 activation next time they are activated. Enemies get +1 str when attacking the knocked down enemy<br>
<em>3-4</em> <strong>Stunned</strong>, Warrior loses entire activation next time they are activated. Enemies get a +2 str when attacking the Stunned enemy<br>
<em>5-6</em> <strong>Out of Action</strong>, remove the warrior from play as they fall to the ground unconscious and badly hurt. <br>
<em>e.g. A warrior has 5 wounds left and takes 7 from a single attack, the warrior who is attacking rolls a D6 and adds +2 to the chart (5-7 = -2, or two below zero)</em><br><br>
If the Warrior is not taken Out of Action immediately they are returned to 1 wound. 
</p>



